About four grand,
and a bottle of 25-year-old
Scotch from 9D.

05:40.485 --> 05:42.487
I'm putting it all in
commercial paper like you said.

05:42.696 --> 05:44.864
Good, but just until
the deutsche mark turns.

05:44.989 --> 05:47.492
- Thank you, Mr. Campbell.
- All right.

06:29.572 --> 06:31.907
Good morning, Joe.
Merry Christmas, sir.

06:37.120 --> 06:40.540
Campbell wants
these available.
Thanks, Adelle.

06:40.624 --> 06:42.542
Better you than me.

06:44.794 --> 06:49.048
If Med Tech shares fall
any lower than 43,

06:49.173 --> 06:51.050
we're in trouble
with the stock valuations.

06:51.175 --> 06:54.887
So for God's sake,
please watch what you say
to your institutional customers.

06:55.012 --> 07:00.392
We still have almost a full day
of trading before zero hour,
and I don't want any trouble.

07:02.018 --> 07:04.437
[ Sighs ]
A penny for
your thoughts, Alan.

07:04.521 --> 07:07.732
Hmm ? Oh, God, I'm sorry.

07:07.815 --> 07:10.735
Jack, I was thinking about,
you know, Dee and the kids.

07:10.818 --> 07:13.070
I promised
I'd be home for dinner.
It's Christmas eve, Jack.

07:13.195 --> 07:16.657
- Oh, is that tonight ?
- [ Polite Laughter ]

07:16.782 --> 07:19.951
You think I like being
here on Christmas eve, Alan ?

07:20.035 --> 07:22.329
No. Well, maybe.

07:22.495 --> 07:25.873
[ Laughter ]
Okay.

07:25.999 --> 07:30.294
Okay, maybe I do have
a touch of tunnel vision
this holiday season.

07:30.378 --> 07:32.630
But in two days
we're going to announce...

07:32.713 --> 07:35.883
one of the largest mergers
in U.S. corporate history.

07:35.966 --> 07:39.803
When a deal like this turns up,
you get on it and you ride it
till it's over.

07:39.886 --> 07:43.598
You don't ask it
for a vacation.

07:43.681 --> 07:46.768
December 26. After that
there'll be so much money
floating around here,

07:46.934 --> 07:48.811
it'll be like Christmas
every day.

07:48.936 --> 07:53.274
December 26, people. If you'd
like to celebrate that day,
you all have my blessing.

07:53.399 --> 07:56.401
- You're right. I'm sorry.
- I don't want you to be sorry.
I want you to be excited.

07:56.568 --> 07:59.154
I want my gift to you
to be the first gift you open
this year. You know why ?

07:59.279 --> 08:02.991
- [ Stammering ]
- Because my gift comes
with ten zeroes.

08:03.116 --> 08:05.952
You're right.
I'm focused. I'm there.

08:06.035 --> 08:08.871
Good man. Everybody,
turn to page 12
in your prospectus.

08:11.499 --> 08:14.418
[ All Chattering Indistinctly ]

08:16.837 --> 08:20.006
You have six messages.
Two of them are imperative.
Whoa. I'm going home.

08:20.090 --> 08:23.176
I'm not even here now.
Good night. Merry Christmas.
Merry Christmas.

08:23.301 --> 08:26.137
It's only 8:30.
I'm disappointed. Got some
last-minute shopping to do ?

08:26.220 --> 08:30.308
You too ? This holiday's about
giving. I'm giving everything
I've got to this deal.

08:30.433 --> 08:34.645
So in a way, I'm more
Christmassy than anybody.
You're my role model, Jack.

08:36.772 --> 08:39.191
Oh, and Oxford called.
Ooh, my suits are ready.

08:39.316 --> 08:41.525
- Mm-hmm.
- Care for a Lifesaver ?

08:41.610 --> 08:43.820
No, thank you.
Help yourself.

08:49.575 --> 08:53.871
Kate Reynolds.
Her assistant said you could
reach her at home after 8:00.

08:53.954 --> 08:56.457
Kate Reynolds was
my girlfriend in college.

08:56.540 --> 08:58.583
I almost married her.
[ Chuckles ]
You ?

08:58.667 --> 09:01.002
Married ?
Almost married.

09:01.127 --> 09:04.881
And almost a broker
at E.F. Hutton.
Excuse me ?

09:05.006 --> 09:08.217
She didn't want me
to go to London.

09:08.342 --> 09:12.138
We're standing at the airport
saying good-bye,
and she asked me to stay.

09:12.221 --> 09:13.931
So you left her.

09:14.014 --> 09:18.018
- Wasn't easy.
- Oh, stop it.
I'm getting all weepy.

09:18.143 --> 09:20.187
I took the road
less traveled, Adelle.

09:20.270 --> 09:24.732
And look where it took ya.
I'm gonna get this gal
on the phone.

09:28.027 --> 09:31.697
Nope.
You almost married
this woman.

09:31.822 --> 09:33.782
You're not even curious
why she called ?

09:33.866 --> 09:36.118
She's probably just having
a fit of nostalgia.

09:36.243 --> 09:40.622
Lonely Christmas eve. Called
the one that got away. Why
call her back and mislead her ?

09:40.747 --> 09:43.124
This happened
a very, very long time ago.

09:43.249 --> 09:46.002
8:35 on Christmas eve.

09:46.085 --> 09:48.254
Jack Campbell still
at his desk.

09:48.379 --> 09:51.590
Now there's
a Hallmark moment for you.

09:51.674 --> 09:54.677
Peter, I don't see you
rushing home to trim the tree.

09:54.802 --> 09:59.556
That's because
I'm a heartless bastard
who only cares about money.

09:59.681 --> 10:02.100
Well, you know what ?
God love you for that.

10:04.144 --> 10:07.438
Got a call
from Terry Haight.

10:07.563 --> 10:09.982
Bob Thomas is nervous.

10:10.066 --> 10:13.611
That'll happen when you're
about to spend $130 billion
on some aspirin.

10:13.777 --> 10:16.447
Somebody's gotta
nurse him through this.

10:16.613 --> 10:18.824
Why are you staring
at my breasts, Peter ?

10:18.907 --> 10:20.826
I need you, tiger.
Where is he ?

10:20.951 --> 10:24.245
- Aspen.
- Call Aunt Irma and tell her
I won't be able to make it.

10:24.370 --> 10:27.081
You're a credit
to capitalism, Jack.

10:27.165 --> 10:29.083
Hey, Peter, let me
ask you a question.

10:29.167 --> 10:32.461
An old girlfriend
calls you out of the blue
on Christmas eve.

10:32.545 --> 10:36.215
- What do you do ?
- You suddenly having trouble
getting dates ?

10:36.298 --> 10:40.552
- Yeah.
- Leave it in the past.

10:40.635 --> 10:43.805
Old flames are like
old tax returns--

10:43.972 --> 10:47.016
put 'em in the file cabinet
for three years, and then
you cut 'em loose.

10:50.478 --> 10:52.980
I'll leave from my office
tomorrow in the afternoon.

10:53.063 --> 10:56.275
Call the group.
Schedule an emergency
strategy session for noon.

10:56.358 --> 10:59.236
That'll be a nice
little holiday treat.

11:24.008 --> 11:26.427
Good night, Frank.
Hey, Mr. Campbell.

11:26.511 --> 11:29.305
Why didn't you call down ?
I would have had Joe
get your ride.

11:29.430 --> 11:31.849
I'm thinking I'll walk tonight.
It's a nice night for it.

11:32.016 --> 11:33.976
I'll send your car
home for you.
That'll be fine.

11:34.059 --> 11:36.603
- And Merry Christmas
to you, sir.
- To you too.

12:23.271 --> 12:26.232
Eggnog ?
Yeah, dairy case.
Five dollar.

12:26.357 --> 12:28.276
Okay.

12:39.703 --> 12:42.747
Hey, yo. Y'all
do the lotto here, right ?
Y'all do the lotto here ?

12:42.831 --> 12:45.375
Yeah.
Cool. 'Cause I got a winner,
baby. I got a winner.

12:45.458 --> 12:49.921
Certified, good as gold. I know
lotto keep a lot of brothers
down, but not Cash Money.

12:50.004 --> 12:52.465
Don't do me none, son,
'cause I'd be like--

12:52.548 --> 12:55.551
Bang on the lottery !
You know what I mean ?
It's all good.

12:55.634 --> 12:58.887
Relax, son. Relax.
I got you four numbers.
Check it. Bust it.

12:59.012 --> 13:03.183
6, 14, 16, 49.
That's a winner, son.

13:03.308 --> 13:06.185
$238, B.
Cheddar coming.

13:06.269 --> 13:11.148
Give me my money.
I'm sorry. Your ticket bad.
You draw in the lines.

13:11.232 --> 13:15.277
What are you talking about, B. ?
You draw in the lines with
a pencil. I know about this.

13:15.361 --> 13:19.114
Yo, buster,
check the ticket, son.
No, you get out.

13:19.197 --> 13:22.200
Yo, you ain't even looked
at the ticket. You looking
at me, son. Check the ticket.

13:22.284 --> 13:25.078
You get out now !
You take the ticket
somewhere else !

13:25.161 --> 13:27.372
Next customer in line !

13:27.497 --> 13:30.625
You get out or I call 9-1-1.

13:30.750 --> 13:32.418
Oh, my God !

13:32.585 --> 13:35.796
Check the ticket, stupid.

13:35.879 --> 13:40.217
Look at the ticket.
Shit, now I'm gonna
make you call God.

13:40.342 --> 13:43.928
That's my word. You best
check that ticket, fool!
Let me see the ticket.

13:44.053 --> 13:46.389
Was I talking to you ?

13:46.514 --> 13:49.767
Maybe I'll buy it from you.
You know, make a little
business deal.

13:52.061 --> 13:55.898
Stupid-ass white boy in
$2,000 suit gets capped trying
to be a hero. News at 11:00.

13:55.981 --> 14:00.819
That's what you wanna see ?
You wanna see Cash up in here ?
You want me to set it, son ?

14:00.944 --> 14:02.612
Do you wanna die ?

14:02.612 --> 14:03.738
Do you wanna die ?

14:05.740 --> 14:07.950
Do you want to die ?

14:09.493 --> 14:11.412
No.

14:14.248 --> 14:18.418
Look, I'm talking about
a business deal.

14:18.502 --> 14:21.379
Okay ? I buy the ticket
from you for $200.

14:21.463 --> 14:25.258
I take it to a store where
the guy behind the counter
doesn't have a death wish.

14:25.341 --> 14:28.177
I just made myself
a quick $38.

14:28.261 --> 14:30.721
Like I said, it's--

14:30.805 --> 14:33.015
it's just a business deal.

14:43.233 --> 14:45.109
All right. Yeah.

14:45.193 --> 14:47.111
All right.

14:50.781 --> 14:53.993
You blew it, B.
You blew it.

14:54.118 --> 14:57.996
The ticket was real.
Damn, you had your chance too.

14:59.915 --> 15:02.208
Come on, Jack.
Let's get out of here.

15:15.095 --> 15:18.223
How'd you know my name
was Jack ?

15:18.348 --> 15:21.560
I call
all you guys Jack.

15:21.685 --> 15:24.813
Here. Nice doing
business with ya.

15:26.439 --> 15:28.941
Hey. Hey, um--

15:31.360 --> 15:34.238
What do you want to carry
that gun around for anyway ?

15:34.321 --> 15:37.741
You're just gonna wind up
doing something you regret.

15:37.824 --> 15:40.076
You're talking
to the wrong person
about regrets, Jack.

15:40.160 --> 15:44.664
I mean, there must be
programs out there
and, um, opportunities.

15:44.789 --> 15:48.209
Wait a minute.
Are you actually trying
to save me ?

15:49.961 --> 15:52.296
This is bananas.

15:52.379 --> 15:55.382
This man thinks
I need to be saved, yo !

15:55.507 --> 15:57.384
Well, everybody
needs something.

15:57.509 --> 16:01.096
Yeah ? Well, what
do you need, Jack ?

16:01.179 --> 16:04.974
Me ?
You just said,
everybody needs something.

16:05.099 --> 16:07.226
I got everything I need.

16:07.310 --> 16:10.730
Wow. It must be great
being you.

16:10.896 --> 16:14.441
I'm not saying that you'd be
able to do it without some hard
work, some honest hard work,

16:14.566 --> 16:16.860
and possibly some medicine.

16:20.447 --> 16:22.407
You know, I'm gonna
really enjoy this.

16:22.490 --> 16:25.577
You just remember that
you did this, Jack, okay ?

16:25.660 --> 16:28.204
You brought this
on yourself.

16:31.123 --> 16:33.876
Merry Christmas.
[ Chuckles ]

18:04.292 --> 18:06.836
Mmm, ten more minutes, Jack.

18:08.796 --> 18:10.673
It's Christmas.

18:21.016 --> 18:24.894
#Jingle bells
Santa smells
Rudolph laid an egg #

18:24.978 --> 18:28.648
- # La, la, la, la, la, la
la, la, la, la, la, la ##
- Never mind.

18:28.773 --> 18:31.484
- [ Woman ] Who's here ?
- Rise and shine.

18:31.609 --> 18:34.445
Don't you think
we should open some presents ?

18:34.528 --> 18:38.031
- I think you should give Mama
five more minutes in bed.
- Come on, Dad. Get up.

18:38.115 --> 18:40.742
Can we do that ?
Yea !
It's Christmas !

18:40.826 --> 18:45.580
- It's Christmas !
- Look, your sister's
jumping on the bed.

18:45.705 --> 18:49.166
What is this dog
doing on the bed?
He needs to get off the bed.

18:49.250 --> 18:51.585
Did Santa come ?
I don't know.
We'll have to go see.

18:51.669 --> 18:54.254
- Let's go see the presents.
- You wanna get some presents ?

18:54.338 --> 18:56.381
Mommy just needs
to wake up.

18:56.507 --> 19:00.635
Jack. Strong coffee.

19:08.726 --> 19:11.645
Oh, Jack.
Merry Christmas, dear.

19:13.480 --> 19:15.941
Lorraine. Ed.

19:16.066 --> 19:18.652
Hey, Jack, you old bird dog.
Merry Christmas to ya.

19:18.777 --> 19:21.196
Talk to him. One day a year
away from the Ponderosa.

19:21.321 --> 19:24.032
- I don't think
that's asking too much.
- This is who I am.

19:24.115 --> 19:27.410
Tell her, Jack, for God's sake.
You're the only one around here
that gets me.

19:27.535 --> 19:31.205
- I need some eggnog.
- 'Course you do, sweet thing.
Almost 8:00 in the morning.

19:31.288 --> 19:32.957
Excuse me.
Where you going,
Jack ?

19:38.086 --> 19:41.840
Josh, Annie, giddyup !
Where's my car ?
Where's my Ferrari ?

19:41.923 --> 19:43.842
What ?
Where's my Ferrari ?

19:43.925 --> 19:47.261
What the hell are you talking--
What's he talking about ?
You got a Ferrari ?

19:47.345 --> 19:49.805
Let me borrow your car
and then I promise
I'll have it returned.

19:49.931 --> 19:52.266
My Caddy ?
Drive your own damn car.

19:52.349 --> 19:54.768
Oh, just let him borrow
your precious Cadillac,
for God sakes.

19:54.893 --> 19:58.397
There's a perfectly
good minivan sitting out there
in the driveway. Here.

19:58.522 --> 20:01.066
What the hell's wrong
with him anyway ?

20:29.508 --> 20:32.887
- Tony, thank God !
- Sorry, pal. Entrance is for
residents and guests only.

20:32.970 --> 20:37.057
What ? What are
you talking about ?

20:37.182 --> 20:40.519
Jack Campbell, penthouse "C."
What's the matter with you ?
Uh-huh.

20:40.644 --> 20:43.772
Mrs. Peterson, I think
there's something wrong
with our man Tony here.

20:43.897 --> 20:45.815
Who is this man ?

20:45.898 --> 20:49.318
Oh, come on.
What is going on
with you two this morning ?

20:49.402 --> 20:53.781
Is this like a, uh--
a Christmas joke ?

20:53.864 --> 20:57.117
"Who is this man ?"
Well, we're on the co-op board
together, Betty.

20:57.201 --> 20:59.494
And we fought side by side
for garbage disposals.

20:59.578 --> 21:02.872
And every morning we exchange
quasi-sexual witty banter.

21:02.998 --> 21:05.542
Okay ?
Shall I call the cops ?
I'm gonna call the cops.

21:05.625 --> 21:08.127
No, I'm gonna call the cops !
You're scaring me.

21:08.252 --> 21:11.005
- No, no, no, no.
- Thank you for not
calling the cops.

21:11.088 --> 21:13.757
Now, I'm going upstairs,
I'm gonna get some sleep.
Then I'll be fine.

21:13.841 --> 21:16.426
Sleep you shall.
Noblesse oblige isn't dead.
Not yet anyway.

21:16.552 --> 21:20.722
Let's, um--Let's get you
some help. Surely there's a
shelter somewhere in this city.

21:20.847 --> 21:22.807
A shelter ?

21:22.932 --> 21:26.978
Hey, hey, are you
smacked out of your head ?

21:27.103 --> 21:30.439
I'm the richest man in
this building ! I've got twice
the square footage you have !

21:30.523 --> 21:33.150
And I'm going upstairs.
Take a walk, pal.

21:33.275 --> 21:35.944
Oh, not cool.
Not cool !

21:36.028 --> 21:38.530
You wanna get cute ?
Get cute.

21:38.655 --> 21:41.700
I'm gonna go to my office.
I'm gonna file a complaint
to the manager of the building.

21:41.866 --> 21:46.579
I'm gonna have you fired, Tony.
And, Mrs. Peterson, you're on
notice with the co-op board !

21:46.704 --> 21:50.416
So you better just stop
whatever this is
that you're doing !

21:54.211 --> 21:57.130
[ Engine Not Starting ]

21:58.090 --> 22:01.218
Oh, yeah.
Oh. Oh, yeah.

22:01.343 --> 22:04.012
Oh, come on !
[ Starts ]

22:11.727 --> 22:15.105
Frank, you won't believe
what's been happening to me.
Is Adelle here yet ?

22:15.189 --> 22:17.107
Hold it right there.
Where's Mintz ?

22:17.191 --> 22:20.318
The building is closed, pal.
You have to come back tomorrow.

22:20.402 --> 22:24.989
Frank, why do I feel
the need to remind you that
I'm Jack Campbell, President ?

22:25.114 --> 22:29.911
I don't care who you are.
It's Christmas, and like I told
you, the building is closed.

22:29.994 --> 22:32.037
I don't think
you heard me correctly.

22:32.163 --> 22:34.748
I'm Jack Campbell.

22:34.832 --> 22:37.042
Jack Campbell !

22:39.002 --> 22:40.921
President !

22:48.761 --> 22:51.138
Have a nice holiday, man.

