a lot of guys have to throw up.
I seen it happen before.

23:49.775 --> 23:53.279
So if you feel the urge,
you roll down the window
and do it out there.

23:53.362 --> 23:56.365
[ Groaning ]
Try not to get
so worked up, Jack.

23:56.490 --> 23:58.367
After all, you brought
this on yourself.

23:58.492 --> 24:00.577
Brought what on myself ?
I didn't do anything !

24:00.660 --> 24:04.080
" I got everything I need."
That sound familiar ?

24:04.205 --> 24:08.543
You mean 'cause you thought
I was cocky, I'm now on
a permanent acid trip ?

24:08.668 --> 24:11.379
Bag yourself, Jack.

24:12.588 --> 24:14.882
[ Screaming ]

24:14.965 --> 24:17.676
Oh, my God! Ah !

24:17.759 --> 24:21.471
The way you intervened
in that store last night, you
did a good thing there, Jack.

24:21.555 --> 24:25.391
I mean, it was
incredibly impressive all
the way across the board...

24:25.475 --> 24:27.143
Oh, God !
to the upper echelons
of the organization.

24:27.268 --> 24:30.855
Please just tell me
what's happening to me
in plain English...

24:30.980 --> 24:33.732
without the mumbo-jumbo.

24:33.816 --> 24:37.361
This is a glimpse, Jack.
A glimpse ?

24:37.486 --> 24:39.905
I--A glimpse of what ?

24:40.071 --> 24:42.907
You're gonna have to
figure that out for yourself
and you got plenty of time.

24:43.033 --> 24:44.701
- How much time ?
- As much time as it takes,

24:44.784 --> 24:46.911
which in your case is probably
gonna be considerable.

24:46.994 --> 24:50.623
Okay, look, look. I-I-I
just want my life back, okay ?

24:50.748 --> 24:54.084
Now, what's it gonna take ?
You wanna talk turkey ?

24:54.168 --> 24:56.837
Let's talk turkey.
How much money ?

24:56.962 --> 25:00.549
- It doesn't work like that,
and I can't tell you why.
- Why not ?

25:00.674 --> 25:03.593
Because you have to figure
this thing out for yourself.

25:03.718 --> 25:06.929
Are you listening to me ?
Figure it out, figure it out.
Figure out what ?

25:07.013 --> 25:10.266
- Let it come to you, man.
- I don't have time for this
right now.

25:10.433 --> 25:14.395
- I'm in the middle of a deal.
- Well, you're working on
a new deal now, baby.

25:18.565 --> 25:20.484
What's this ?
Open it.

25:20.567 --> 25:23.236
What is it,
some kind of a signal ?

25:25.280 --> 25:28.699
[ Bell Dings ]
Will you come
whenever I ring it ?

25:28.783 --> 25:30.785
Now you gotta
get out of the car, Jack.

25:33.329 --> 25:36.665
But what do I do ?
I'm sorry. I can't spend
any more time with you.

25:36.790 --> 25:40.418
I got some other business
I gotta take care of.
No, y-y-you did this to me.

25:40.544 --> 25:42.671
You can't just
leave me like this.

25:46.424 --> 25:49.719
Okay. Look, you wanna
get some air ? Let's get
outside, get some air.

25:49.802 --> 25:52.763
We'll walk and I'll explain
everything to you, okay ?

25:54.890 --> 25:57.559
- Thanks, man.
- Sure.

26:48.981 --> 26:51.734
Excuse me. Do you know
where Merrison Street is ?

26:51.859 --> 26:53.944
[ Chuckles ]
Jeannie.

26:54.111 --> 26:56.780
I found Jack.
Oh, there you are, stranger.

26:57.990 --> 27:00.367
Where you been ?

27:04.037 --> 27:06.289
[ Sighs ]

27:06.414 --> 27:09.750
You look terrible.
Truth is, I expected you.

27:09.834 --> 27:13.420
Kate called and asked
if I knew where you were, so--

27:16.465 --> 27:20.260
Oh, I put the Barcalounger
in the center of the room.
It's throwing everybody off.

27:20.343 --> 27:22.262
What do you think ?

27:26.099 --> 27:28.518
It's a great room.
Great room.

27:28.643 --> 27:30.436
You and me, buddy,
we know how to live, huh ?

27:30.519 --> 27:32.396
Come on.

27:34.315 --> 27:37.442
Come on, Jack.
Come on--

27:37.568 --> 27:39.945
Whoo !
[ Laughing ]

27:41.780 --> 27:44.282
Come on, buddy.
Take your seat.

27:51.580 --> 27:54.041
Are you okay ?

27:54.166 --> 27:57.961
I mean, you take off Christmas
morning and you don't tell
anyone where you're going.

28:01.715 --> 28:05.426
- We're friends ?
- Talk to me.

28:09.222 --> 28:11.432
I'm having kind of
a bad day.

28:11.515 --> 28:15.060
You know, I read somewhere
that the suicide rate doubles
during the holiday.

28:15.185 --> 28:17.980
What am I saying that for ?
You don't wanna hear that.
Come on.

28:20.482 --> 28:22.817
Is it--
Is it trouble at work ?

28:24.110 --> 28:26.112
I--I don't think so.

28:26.195 --> 28:28.156
Well, it's not Kate,
is it ?

28:31.659 --> 28:34.787
You see, huh ?
It's like we're inside
each other's heads.

28:36.038 --> 28:37.956
Kate's my wife.
[ Chuckles ]

28:38.040 --> 28:42.335
Just keep saying it over
and over again, Jack,
like a mantra. Keep saying it.

28:49.467 --> 28:51.802
Look, you know,
you fit the profile exactly--

28:51.886 --> 28:56.265
in your 30s, house, kids,
financial responsibilities.

28:56.390 --> 28:59.684
You start thinking
this isn't the life
I dreamt about.

28:59.810 --> 29:02.520
Where's the romance,
you know ?

29:02.687 --> 29:05.064
Where's the joie de vivre ?

29:06.566 --> 29:10.528
Suddenly every lingerie ad
in the Newark Star-Ledger...

29:10.611 --> 29:13.197
represents a life
that you can't have.

29:16.325 --> 29:18.535
It's just two kids,
right ?

29:21.496 --> 29:24.124
Come on. Come on.

29:24.207 --> 29:27.919
All right, sometimes
it feels like you gave up
the whole world. I know that.

29:28.044 --> 29:31.380
But look what you got.
Look at that:
four bedrooms,

29:31.505 --> 29:34.550
two-and-a-half baths,
a partially finished basement.

29:34.675 --> 29:37.636
And good kids.
Look. You know what ?

29:37.803 --> 29:40.096
You probably don't wanna
hear this right now.

29:40.222 --> 29:43.975
But remember last summer when
I almost had that thing with
Arnie, Jr.'s speech therapist ?

29:44.058 --> 29:45.935
You remember what
you said to me ?

29:48.146 --> 29:50.898
You said, " Don't screw up
the best thing in your life...

29:51.023 --> 29:53.859
just because
you're a little unsure
about who you are."

29:53.984 --> 29:55.903
Okay ?

30:04.911 --> 30:07.413
Go get 'em, tiger.

30:40.652 --> 30:42.654
Could you hold on
a second?

30:50.828 --> 30:55.040
Um, never mind because--
because he just walked in.

30:55.124 --> 30:57.334
Thank you. Thank you.

31:00.629 --> 31:04.215
Do you... have any idea
what you put us through today ?

31:05.425 --> 31:07.844
You walk out of here
at 7:30 in the morning.

31:08.010 --> 31:11.806
You don't tell me
where you're going,
or even that you're going.

31:11.889 --> 31:14.308
And I don't see you
till hours later ?

31:14.391 --> 31:17.811
I called all of our friends.
I had the state troopers
looking for you.

31:17.936 --> 31:20.981
I was on the phone
with the hospital,
for God's sakes.

31:21.189 --> 31:25.860
What kind of man leaves his
family Christmas morning without
a word about where he's going ?

31:25.944 --> 31:29.197
What kind of a man
does that, Jack ?
I don't know.

31:29.363 --> 31:32.491
Could you--Could you please
stop yelling at me ?

31:36.787 --> 31:40.248
Where were you ?
I was in the city.

31:40.373 --> 31:43.668
The city ?
New York City ?

31:43.793 --> 31:46.004
Yeah.
Why ?

31:50.508 --> 31:53.469
Because that's where I live.
Don't start, Jack.
Don't.

31:53.552 --> 31:55.971
Look, you don't understand.

31:56.054 --> 31:59.266
I--I--I woke up
this morning here.

32:01.059 --> 32:04.187
And this is very strange
because...

32:04.270 --> 32:06.189
this isn't my house.

32:06.272 --> 32:09.317
[ Groans ]
And those aren't my kids.
I'm not Dad.

32:09.400 --> 32:12.862
I-I-I'm not a dad.
You're not my wife.

32:12.945 --> 32:15.364
You know what, Jack.
It's not funny this time...

32:15.489 --> 32:17.366
because I am really mad.

32:17.449 --> 32:19.951
I mean, really mad.
I mean it.

32:20.076 --> 32:22.454
I don't even--
[ Bell Dinging ]

32:25.331 --> 32:27.708
What--

32:27.792 --> 32:29.961
What's that ?

32:34.089 --> 32:37.050
I like it.
Thanks, Dad.

32:37.175 --> 32:39.636
That's mine. Hey,
I need that back.

32:39.761 --> 32:41.972
She took my bell.

32:43.223 --> 32:45.600
You missed the whole thing--

32:45.725 --> 32:48.436
the pancakes
and the presents.

32:48.519 --> 32:52.022
You spent six hours
putting that bike together
for Annie,

32:52.148 --> 32:55.692
and then you didn't even
get to see the look on her face
when she opened it.

32:57.194 --> 33:00.071
You missed Christmas, Jack.

33:03.908 --> 33:05.785
I'm sorry.

33:07.829 --> 33:10.956
[ Sniffles ]
You know, we don't even
have enough time for this.

33:11.040 --> 33:14.293
And at least you're okay.
I'm okay, we're okay.

33:14.418 --> 33:18.588
But you've gotta get dressed
for the Thompson party.
And you are not wearing that.

33:18.672 --> 33:20.882
I don't care how hilarious
you think it is.

33:21.007 --> 33:23.468
Party ? No, I'm not
going to a party.

33:23.593 --> 33:26.888
You look forward
to this party all year.
What is it with you today ?

33:27.013 --> 33:30.141
Believe me, Kate.
I really don't think
that going to a party...

33:30.266 --> 33:32.518
is the right move for me
at the present time.

33:32.643 --> 33:36.772
Okay, fine. You know what ?
Then you just do
whatever you wanna do.

33:36.855 --> 33:40.859
What are you doing ?
Telling my mother she doesn't
have to stay with the kids.

33:40.984 --> 33:43.695
Why not ?
Because you'll be here.

33:48.574 --> 33:50.576
I'll be ready in ten minutes.
[ Sighs ]

33:51.827 --> 33:53.704
[ Groans ]

33:57.583 --> 34:02.253
This is--This is
just subpar.

