- Big Ed's.

44:44.968 --> 44:48.846
Big Ed's Tires ?
Why ?

44:48.930 --> 44:52.766
- 'Cause you work there.
- You mean I sell tires.

44:54.059 --> 44:58.063
That's what I do.
I'm a tire salesman.

45:06.404 --> 45:08.322
Good Lord !

45:35.264 --> 45:37.557
- Morning, Jack.
- Hi.

45:41.269 --> 45:44.355
- Good morning, Jack.
- Hi.

45:44.480 --> 45:46.482
Hey, Jack.

45:50.361 --> 45:53.239
## [ "Sleigh Ride" ]

45:55.657 --> 45:58.285
Jack, my boy.

45:58.410 --> 46:01.496
Hey, guess who I played
bridge with two nights ago.

46:01.621 --> 46:03.915
Hell, you'll never guess.

46:03.998 --> 46:08.419
One Sydney Potter.
That's Sydney Potter,
C.E.O., Buy Rite Transport.

46:08.544 --> 46:11.589
Only the third biggest
trucking outfit in the state.

46:11.714 --> 46:15.217
"Any hoo, " he's looking
for a new parts supplier.

46:15.342 --> 46:17.970
We can handle volume
like that, now can't we, Jack ?

46:19.513 --> 46:22.015
I'm gonna have to
get back to you on that, Ed.

46:22.182 --> 46:24.559
Right on.
[ Clicks Tongue ]

46:24.642 --> 46:26.519
Right on.

46:33.901 --> 46:38.822
Excuse me. Uh, do I--
do I have a private office
somewhere in the building ?

46:39.906 --> 46:42.701
Sure, Jack.

46:42.784 --> 46:44.702
Where is it ?

46:44.786 --> 46:47.246
Oh, uh, it's--

46:47.330 --> 46:49.332
it's right back--
right back there.

46:49.415 --> 46:52.168
Thank you.
Yeah.

47:14.646 --> 47:16.607
[ Groans ]

47:30.453 --> 47:32.371
Oh, no.

47:42.005 --> 47:45.842
You must've needed this
every day.

47:59.104 --> 48:00.939
[ Sighs ]

48:05.443 --> 48:07.653
[ Cup Clatters On Floor ]

48:12.199 --> 48:15.369
What are you smiling about ?

48:18.205 --> 48:20.916
Eighty-eight ?

48:23.334 --> 48:25.920
I was in London in 1988.

48:30.674 --> 48:33.344
You never went to London.

48:36.263 --> 48:40.350
[ Woman Over P.A., Loudly ]
Jack, you're needed in mag
wheels. Customer waiting.

48:45.271 --> 48:50.401
I was the number one
junior sales associate
for E.F. Hutton in 1988.

48:50.526 --> 48:53.028
Did you know that ?
Uh, no.
No, I didn't.

48:53.153 --> 48:55.030
That's great.

48:55.155 --> 48:57.699
That's the kind of thing
you could really build on,
you know ?

48:57.783 --> 49:02.537
Uh-huh. Yeah.
I mean, sales has always been
a feeder for M&A. Always.

49:02.620 --> 49:04.455
Uh-huh.

49:04.622 --> 49:08.084
Well, look, here we are.
The mag wheels. Mag wheels.

49:08.251 --> 49:10.127
Oh.
So.

49:10.252 --> 49:14.048
Hey, Jack, um,
are you sure you're okay ?

49:14.131 --> 49:17.759
Well, I'm just
a little confused right now
about why I work here.

49:17.884 --> 49:20.137
Uh--
[ Chuckles ]

49:20.220 --> 49:23.681
I just started here
last Tuesday, so--

49:30.604 --> 49:33.691
[ Woman On TV ]
The closing tip was
a mildly bullish plus-76.

49:33.774 --> 49:37.236
Much of the market's action
today was fueled by the latest
round of merger mania...

49:37.402 --> 49:39.154
to hit Wall Street...

49:39.279 --> 49:42.532
when Global Health Systems
and Med Tech Pharmaceutical
announced their intentions...

49:42.615 --> 49:47.245
to join forces in a massive
$122 billion stock swap deal,

49:47.328 --> 49:49.580
the largest ever
in the health care industry.

49:49.664 --> 49:52.458
When asked about the possible
anti-competitive implications,

49:52.541 --> 49:55.294
Global chairman Bob Thomas
referred reporters...

49:55.377 --> 49:59.673
to P.K. Lassiter & Company
president Alan Mintz,
the architect behind the deal.

49:59.798 --> 50:03.843
- That's my deal !
- Ironically, Mintz first met
Thomas at a Lamaze class.

50:03.968 --> 50:06.512
While coaching their pregnant
wives, Mintz and Thomas...
What ?

50:06.596 --> 50:09.765
struck up a dialog,
and two months later,
the deal with Med Tech was born.

50:09.890 --> 50:12.851
He wasn't the architect !
I'm the architect !

50:12.977 --> 50:17.773
Labor department officials
announced today that 275,000
new jobs have been created.

50:17.856 --> 50:20.859
The kids are asleep.
[ Chuckles ]

50:20.984 --> 50:23.236
The kids, hon.
Honey.

50:24.445 --> 50:28.282
Sweetheart, I said
the kids are asleep.

50:28.366 --> 50:32.453
That's just great.
Those little monkeys
can be a real handful.

50:32.578 --> 50:35.414
Hey, I was watching that.

50:35.497 --> 50:38.417
Not tonight.
## [ Stereo ]

50:38.500 --> 50:40.961
[ Chuckles ]

50:41.086 --> 50:44.214
Please leave
my socks alone.
[ Laughing ]

50:51.762 --> 50:53.931
Wait.
[ Chuckles ]

50:54.098 --> 50:57.893
- You want me.
- That is the general idea,
yeah.

50:59.769 --> 51:02.939
Oh, well, maybe we should
grab a bottle of wine first.

51:03.022 --> 51:05.024
[ Laughs ]
Kind of break the ice.

51:05.108 --> 51:08.277
Yeah, that's very funny.
Look, it's 10:30.

51:08.402 --> 51:11.113
By 11:00 you're gonna be
snoring like a monster,

51:11.197 --> 51:13.240
but that's very sweet.

51:13.324 --> 51:15.784
I'll remember that
for next time.

51:15.909 --> 51:18.704
Whatever you say...
honey.

51:18.870 --> 51:20.830
[ Chuckling ]
Yeah.

51:20.956 --> 51:25.793
#Strange what desire
will make foolish people do #

51:29.380 --> 51:33.676
# I never dreamed
that I'd need somebody #

51:33.801 --> 51:35.677
# Like you #

51:37.471 --> 51:39.764
Oh, God, you're beautiful.

51:39.848 --> 51:41.850
Thanks, Jack.

51:41.975 --> 51:45.353
No, I'm serious.

51:45.478 --> 51:47.355
You're really stunning.

51:47.480 --> 51:49.732
This is good stuff.
I want you to keep this up.

51:49.815 --> 51:53.777
You were always
a very pretty girl in college.
There's no question about that.

51:55.112 --> 51:57.656
But this--

51:57.781 --> 52:02.535
[ Sighs ]
You've really grown
into a beautiful woman.

52:02.660 --> 52:05.413
How can you do that ?

52:06.789 --> 52:08.708
What ?

52:08.791 --> 52:13.003
Look at me like you
haven't seen me every day
for the last 13 years.

52:17.591 --> 52:20.510
Okay, wait. Don't move.
Don't look.

52:20.635 --> 52:22.762
Stay right there.
[ Chuckling ]

52:22.887 --> 52:24.764
I got something.

52:52.748 --> 52:54.875
# The world was on fire #

52:55.000 --> 52:57.544
# No one could save me
but you #

52:57.711 --> 52:59.588
[ Whispering ]
Good night, sweetheart.

53:01.298 --> 53:03.258
#Strange what desire #

53:03.341 --> 53:06.594
# Will make foolish people do ##

53:08.346 --> 53:10.264
## [ Stops ]

53:46.672 --> 53:48.591
Okay, we're almost
out of here.

53:48.674 --> 53:51.552
Mary Janes, Mommy.
You promised.

53:51.635 --> 53:54.722
That's right.
I did promise.
Okay. All right.

53:54.805 --> 53:57.391
We're gonna stop
at the kids' shoe
department first,

53:57.516 --> 54:01.019
and then I gotta
pick up my watch
from the battery store.

54:01.144 --> 54:02.979
Then I'm gonna go
to the linen store.

54:03.063 --> 54:05.231
Why don't we go
to all the stores ?

54:05.356 --> 54:08.401
Every single store
in this god forsaken
shopping mall.

54:08.568 --> 54:10.444
Wouldn't that
be exciting ?

54:12.154 --> 54:14.823
You know what ?
Why don't I take the kids,

54:14.948 --> 54:18.827
and you just stay here
and hang out
in the men's department ?

54:18.910 --> 54:21.371
Come on, hon.

54:38.345 --> 54:41.473
It's perfect
for your frame.

54:41.598 --> 54:44.058
Why don't you try it on ?

54:47.478 --> 54:51.732
I might want to take
an inch out of the back.
Okay.

54:51.816 --> 54:53.734
Lengthen the sleeve.

54:57.279 --> 54:59.739
You look amazing
in that suit.

55:02.283 --> 55:05.203
I mean, really--
wow !

55:05.286 --> 55:08.664
Off the charts, great.

55:08.748 --> 55:11.000
It's an unbelievable thing.

55:11.125 --> 55:14.962
Wearing this suit
actually makes me feel
like a better person.

55:21.426 --> 55:23.344
I'm gonna buy it.

55:26.139 --> 55:29.100
It's $2, 400.

55:29.225 --> 55:32.228
Are you out of your mind ?
Come on, let's go.

55:32.353 --> 55:35.689
She got those shoes.
Those shoes were $25.

55:35.814 --> 55:37.983
Come on.
Take it off, all right ?

55:38.108 --> 55:40.944
We'll go to the food court
and get one of those
funnel cakes you like.

55:41.027 --> 55:43.154
Daddy's a crazy guy.

55:43.321 --> 55:45.198
No.

55:47.325 --> 55:49.201
[ Whispers ]
No.

55:51.829 --> 55:54.873
Do you have any idea
what my life is like ?

55:54.957 --> 55:59.628
- Excuse me ?
- I wake up in the morning
covered in dog saliva.

55:59.753 --> 56:01.671
I drop the kids off,

56:01.755 --> 56:04.465
spend eight hours
selling tires retail.

56:04.549 --> 56:06.467
Retail, Kate.

56:06.551 --> 56:10.096
I pick the kids up,
walk the dog,

56:10.221 --> 56:13.140
which, by the way,
carries the added bonus...

56:13.265 --> 56:17.227
of carting away
her monstrous crap.

56:17.394 --> 56:20.522
I play with the kids,
take out the garbage,

56:20.689 --> 56:22.565
get six hours of sleep
if I'm lucky.

56:22.690 --> 56:24.567
Then everything starts
all over again.

56:24.651 --> 56:26.319
So what's in it for me ?

56:26.444 --> 56:29.280
Wh-Where are my Mary Janes ?

56:31.824 --> 56:35.202
You know, it's sad to hear
that your life is such
a disappointment to you.

56:35.285 --> 56:38.497
I can't believe it isn't
a disappointment to you!

56:38.622 --> 56:42.751
Jesus, Kate, I could
have been a thousand times
the man I became.

56:42.834 --> 56:45.503
I could have been
one of the richest--
Forbes--

56:45.628 --> 56:51.133
How could you do this to me ?
How could you let me give up
on my dreams like this ?

56:51.258 --> 56:55.095
Really, I want to know.

56:55.220 --> 56:57.180
Who are you ?

56:57.264 --> 57:00.183
All right, look.
I'm sorry.

57:00.267 --> 57:03.812
[ Clears Throat ]
I'm sorry I was such
a saint before...

57:03.895 --> 57:05.813
and I'm such a prick now !

57:05.897 --> 57:08.149
But maybe I'm just not...

57:08.274 --> 57:11.861
the same guy that I was
when we got married.

57:11.986 --> 57:14.113
You know what ?
Maybe you're not.

57:14.196 --> 57:19.117
Because the Jack Campbell
I married would not need
a $2, 400 suit...

57:19.201 --> 57:21.620
to feel better
about his life.

57:21.745 --> 57:25.081
But I'm telling you,
if that's what it's
gonna take, then buy it.

57:25.206 --> 57:28.793
Jesus !
We 'll take the money out
of the kids' college fund.

57:28.918 --> 57:32.338
Forget it.
We'll get a funnel cake.

57:32.421 --> 57:35.340
It'll be the highlight
of my week.

57:50.730 --> 57:53.399
Listen, I'm really sorry
about that back in the store.

57:53.482 --> 57:55.400
I don't want to fight
with you.

57:55.484 --> 58:00.155
I just sometimes wonder
how we ended up here,
you know.

58:00.322 --> 58:03.783
I mean, back in college,
d-did you see us here ?

58:03.908 --> 58:07.036
Life has thrown us
a few surprises.
I'll give you that.

58:07.120 --> 58:10.623
It really has, hasn't it ?

58:10.706 --> 58:14.376
Yeah. So, if you had to,
what would you say
was the biggest surprise ?

58:14.460 --> 58:18.422
Just out of curiosity.
I'm just asking.

58:18.505 --> 58:23.259
- Well, Annie, for one.
- Surprise, we're pregnant.

58:23.384 --> 58:25.303
Yeah, that must have been.

58:25.386 --> 58:29.473
I mean, that--that was.
That was a very
unexpected moment.

58:29.598 --> 58:33.894
- What are you gonna do ?
- I think it turned out
all right, don't you ?

58:34.019 --> 58:36.063
Yeah.
I really like Annie.

58:36.188 --> 58:38.106
Well, good, Jack.
Maybe we'll keep her.

58:38.190 --> 58:40.108
No, I love her.
I love Annie.

58:40.192 --> 58:42.027
I'm just--

58:43.695 --> 58:46.656
We had a lot of good times,
didn't we ?

58:49.367 --> 58:52.077
Do you remember
the place on Charles Street
where we used to go ?

58:52.203 --> 58:54.496
Charles Street ?

58:56.373 --> 58:58.834
In the village ?

58:58.959 --> 59:01.127
When we were living
in Greenwich Village.

59:01.253 --> 59:05.131
Yeah. Yeah, yeah.
Great times. Great place.

59:05.256 --> 59:07.133
Why did we ever leave ?

59:07.258 --> 59:10.469
You can't really raise a kid
in an apartment in the village.

59:10.594 --> 59:13.514
Then there was the whole trek
out to the hospital.
That didn't help either.

59:16.975 --> 59:20.353
You were great. I mean,
surviving the heart attack
was one thing.

59:20.437 --> 59:22.939
- You had a heart attack ?
- Hey, Jack, stop that.

59:23.064 --> 59:26.692
'Cause I am--
I'm still mad at you.

59:26.776 --> 59:31.322
Who knows what would
have happened if you hadn't
stepped in at the store ?

59:31.405 --> 59:34.241
That's why I work
for Big Ed.

59:36.076 --> 59:39.079
That's why I work
for Big Ed. Yeah.

59:41.623 --> 59:45.001
So we had a baby,
Big Ed had a heart attack.

59:45.084 --> 59:48.045
Bought that house,
and I've been working
for him ever since.

59:48.171 --> 59:50.923
Sayonara, Wall Street.

59:52.591 --> 59:55.010
Our life in a nutshell.

59:55.094 --> 59:57.721
If you want to
look at it that way.

59:57.888 --> 01:00:00.348
How would you look at it ?

01:00:03.184 --> 01:00:06.062
A great success story.

01:00:11.275 --> 01:00:14.653
What do you say, Jack ?
Show 'em how to do it, baby.
Jack, we need a strike.

01:00:16.280 --> 01:00:19.658
- Damn !
-Jesus, Jack.
What are you doing ?

01:00:19.783 --> 01:00:23.786
It's a league match.
Where's your follow through ?
Where's your stance ?

01:00:23.870 --> 01:00:27.039
You know what ?
I'm doing the best I can.

01:00:27.123 --> 01:00:29.375
It's okay, Jack.

01:00:29.458 --> 01:00:31.669
[ Arnie ]
Why am I so competitive
all the time ?

01:00:31.752 --> 01:00:35.047
You can still
pick up that spare.
Crack 'em, Jack !

01:00:35.172 --> 01:00:39.050
Here we go.
Hurt 'em.

01:00:39.134 --> 01:00:42.345
You're Jack Campbell.
You're better than the sport.

01:00:42.470 --> 01:00:45.973
You shot the rapids in Kanai.
You ran with the bulls
in Pamplona.

01:00:46.099 --> 01:00:48.893
You've jumped out of an airplane
over the Mojave Desert,
for Christ's sake.

01:00:49.018 --> 01:00:49.810
You can do this.
You can do this.

01:00:49.810 --> 01:00:51.854
You can do this.
You can do this.

01:00:59.820 --> 01:01:03.198
Yes ! Victorious !

01:01:03.281 --> 01:01:07.076
Ha-ha ? Ah-ha ?
[ Laughing ]

01:01:07.160 --> 01:01:09.245
Huh ? All right!

01:01:09.328 --> 01:01:11.580
High five !

01:01:11.705 --> 01:01:14.917
You're up.
Go get 'em.

01:01:25.051 --> 01:01:27.178
Hi, Jack.

01:01:28.512 --> 01:01:32.391
Evelyn, right ?
[ Laughs ]
Very funny.

01:01:32.516 --> 01:01:35.352
I saw you on lane 20.
You got the flu
or something ?

01:01:35.477 --> 01:01:37.521
Something like that,
yeah.

01:01:37.688 --> 01:01:40.357
Need a nurse ?

01:01:40.440 --> 01:01:42.359
Are you a nurse ?

01:01:42.442 --> 01:01:44.611
If that's what you want.

01:01:46.154 --> 01:01:48.531
Hey, wait a minute.

01:01:48.614 --> 01:01:50.950
Um, don't run away.

01:01:52.952 --> 01:01:54.953
Are we--

01:01:55.079 --> 01:01:57.122
Are we what, Jack ?

01:01:57.247 --> 01:01:59.124
Well--

01:01:59.207 --> 01:02:02.210
Is there something
going on between us ?

01:02:07.632 --> 01:02:10.217
Are we finally
being honest ?

01:02:10.343 --> 01:02:13.387
It would help me
if we were.

01:02:13.512 --> 01:02:15.556
Okay. You're right.

01:02:15.681 --> 01:02:19.810
We've been dancing
around this for years.

01:02:19.893 --> 01:02:22.562
[ Sighs ]
Here goes.

01:02:22.687 --> 01:02:26.357
When I get dressed
for a party, and I know
you're gonna be there,

01:02:26.566 --> 01:02:30.986
let's just say
I don't go strapless
because my husband likes it.

01:02:31.153 --> 01:02:34.740
I've got six sets
of snow tires piled up
in my garage,

01:02:34.865 --> 01:02:38.410
and I won't even drive
in the snow.

01:02:38.493 --> 01:02:41.079
And our kids
just happen to be...

01:02:41.204 --> 01:02:44.582
in the same ballet class
every year.

01:02:44.666 --> 01:02:49.337
So, if you're asking
whether I'd like it
to be more,

01:02:49.462 --> 01:02:52.298
the answer's yes.

01:02:52.381 --> 01:02:54.299
Kate would never
have to know.

01:02:58.512 --> 01:03:00.639
Do I have your number ?

01:03:02.349 --> 01:03:06.019
Steve's out of town
with the kids this weekend.

01:03:06.102 --> 01:03:08.563
Why don't you
just stop by ?

01:03:21.908 --> 01:03:24.327
Hey, Jack.
You're all flushed.

01:03:24.410 --> 01:03:26.996
I feel good.
Guess that 71 took
a lot out of you.

01:03:27.080 --> 01:03:31.167
No. I just saw
Evelyn Thompson.

01:03:31.333 --> 01:03:33.210
She's relentless.

01:03:33.335 --> 01:03:35.587
She wants to have
an affair with me.

01:03:37.673 --> 01:03:40.342
- She said that ?
- Pretty much.

01:03:42.135 --> 01:03:44.387
What is it about you ?

01:03:44.512 --> 01:03:49.975
So... if you would write
her exact address down there.

01:03:50.101 --> 01:03:53.354
You have a pen ? Please.
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hold on a second.

01:03:53.437 --> 01:03:56.940
You're not actually thinking
about cheating on Kate ?

01:03:57.107 --> 01:04:00.318
Well, it wouldn't really
be cheating, Arnie.

01:04:02.195 --> 01:04:03.655
It's complicated.

01:04:03.655 --> 01:04:04.614
It's complicated.

01:04:04.739 --> 01:04:08.326
Maybe I haven't been as good
a consigliere as you've been
to me, but hear me out on this.

01:04:08.492 --> 01:04:10.953
A little flirtation
is harmless,

01:04:11.078 --> 01:04:13.580
but you're dealing
with fire here, man.

01:04:13.664 --> 01:04:16.750
The Fidelity Bank and Trust
is a tough creditor.

01:04:16.875 --> 01:04:20.170
You make a deposit
somewhere else, they
close your account...

01:04:20.253 --> 01:04:22.589
forever, all right ?

01:04:22.672 --> 01:04:24.674
Arnie, I don't want
your head to explode,

01:04:24.757 --> 01:04:27.385
but I'm telling you,
those rules don't apply to me.

01:04:27.468 --> 01:04:29.470
I-I'm not even--

01:04:29.553 --> 01:04:32.848
I'm not talking about rules.
I'm talking about--

01:04:32.973 --> 01:04:34.933
Y-You're--

01:04:35.017 --> 01:04:38.562
There isn't a guy
in Union County who wouldn't
give his left nut...

01:04:38.729 --> 01:04:40.897
to be with Kate,
all right ?

01:04:41.064 --> 01:04:44.400
She's amazing, and you're
gonna fuck it up.

01:04:44.484 --> 01:04:47.612
Just think about that,
all right ?

01:05:01.583 --> 01:05:04.294
Hey, honey.
How was the game ?

01:05:04.419 --> 01:05:06.963
Long and boring
and generally pretty sad.

01:05:08.089 --> 01:05:10.591
Arnie seemed to enjoy it.

01:05:10.716 --> 01:05:13.093
Sort of.

01:05:13.218 --> 01:05:15.637
Hey, where's
that chocolate cake ?

01:05:17.806 --> 01:05:21.518
- Do you mean
this chocolate cake ?
- That's my piece.

01:05:21.643 --> 01:05:25.772
I was saving it because I
got nauseated by that precooked
mini-mall rotisserie chicken.

01:05:25.897 --> 01:05:29.817
Mmm. Mmm.
It's good.

01:05:29.942 --> 01:05:32.152
Give me that cake.

01:05:32.236 --> 01:05:34.405
No way.

01:05:35.697 --> 01:05:38.116
Come on.
I'm sorry.

01:05:38.241 --> 01:05:40.118
It's too important to me.

01:05:49.293 --> 01:05:51.712
# Ta-da ##

01:05:51.837 --> 01:05:55.382
I want that cake !

01:05:55.466 --> 01:05:58.552
You want this cake ?
I want it.

